DESCRIPTION: Remove the green LED from its holder in the power supply module and test it separately with a known good 12V supply and series resistor to determine if the LED is faulty (not lighting up under correct voltage and current).,
RESULT: The PSU green LED diode test returned a nominal forward voltage of 2.1 V, matching the specification. No fault with the LED was detected in this test. The attempt to move the LED failed because the source and target modules were the same.
Current persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:
No circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.


