RESULT: The red indicator LED anode is at 1.2958 V and its cathode is at 0.0043 V, indicating about 1.29 V across the LED. The associated resistor has 11.9635 V on one side and 1.2958 V on the other, for a voltage drop of about 10.67 V across the resistor. No polarity inversion is present in the tested connections.
